  "rationale": "<p>Choice C is correct. If the equation is true for all <span class=\"italic\">x</span>, then the expressions on both sides of the equation will be equivalent. Multiplying the polynomials on the left-hand side of the equation gives <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"5 a, x cubed, minus a, b x squared, plus 4 a, x, plus 15 x squared, minus 3 b x, plus 12\"></span>. On the right-hand side of the equation, the only <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x squared\"></span>-term is <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"negative 9 x squared\"></span>. Since the expressions on both sides of the equation are equivalent, it follows that <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"negative a, b x squared, plus 15 x squared, equals negative 9 x squared\"></span>, which can be rewritten as <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"open parenthesis, negative a, b plus 15, close parenthesis, times x squared, equals negative 9 x squared\"></span>. Therefore, <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"negative a, b plus 15, equals negative 9\"></span>, which gives <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"a, b equals 24\"></span>.<p>Choice A is incorrect. If <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"a, b equals 18\"></span>, then the coefficient of <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x squared\"></span> on the left-hand side of the equation would be <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"negative 18 plus 15, equals negative 3\"></span>, which doesn&rsquo;t equal the coefficient of <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x squared\"></span>, <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"negative 9\"></span>, on the right-hand side. Choice B is incorrect. If <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"a, b equals 20\"></span>, then the coefficient of <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x squared\"></span> on the left-hand side of the equation would be <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"negative 20 plus 15, equals negative 5\"></span>, which doesn&rsquo;t equal the coefficient of <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x squared\"></span>, <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"negative 9\"></span>, on the right-hand side. Choice D is incorrect. If <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"a, b equals 40\"></span>, then the coefficient of <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x squared\"></span> on the left-hand side of the equation would be <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"negative 40 plus 15, equals negative 25\"></span>, which doesn&rsquo;t equal the coefficient of <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x squared\"></span>, <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"negative 9\"></span>, on the right-hand side.</p><p>&nbsp;</p></p>\n",
